## ✨ ITEM 5 — Output tightening (after Item 1 telemetry)

**Goal:** Reduce per-plan output cost by ~10-15% by capping variability on the biggest output drivers. Do this **after** Item 1 has been live long enough to show the actual distribution.

**Files to modify:** `api/_lib/prompts.js`

### Sub-tasks (gated on data)

**5a.** If telemetry shows 80%+ of carousels use ≤5 slides → tighten the prompt from "array of 3-7 slides" to "array of 3-5 slides".

**5b.** If 80%+ of stories use ≤4 frames → tighten "array of 3-5 Story frames" to "array of 3-4 Story frames".

**5c.** If 95th-percentile output tokens < 10000 → lower `maxTokens` from 12000 to 10000 as a safer ceiling.

### Acceptance test

- Median output tokens decreases by the expected amount (10-15%)
- Truncation rate from telemetry does **not** increase
- No regression in qualitative plan richness (sample 5 generations before/after, eyeball)

