## ✨ ITEM 8 — Predictive pre-generation

**Goal:** For users with a regular weekly posting rhythm, pre-generate next week's plan in the background ~30 minutes before their typical "open VIRL" time. User opens app → plan is already there → zero perceived latency.

**Files to modify:** new `api/cron/predictive-plan.js`, `api/chat.js` (accept pre-generated plan reuse), `index.html` (Plan tab reads from `predictive_plans` table on mount)

### Requirements

- User must have 4+ weeks of history to identify their typical generation window
- New Supabase table `predictive_plans` keyed by `(user_id, week_start)`
- Hourly cron identifies eligible users, kicks off plan generation via **Item 7 batches** (half the cost)
- Pre-generated plans expire after 24 hours — stale ones get discarded, user sees normal generation flow

### Tradeoffs

- Significant infra lift (cron, batch polling, dedup logic)
- Wastes credits if user changes habits or skips a week (mitigated by 24h expiry)
- High UX win for power users with rhythm

### Acceptance test

- Cron successfully pre-generates for at least one test user
- Test user opens app at typical time → plan visible within 1s
- User opens app outside their typical window → falls back to live generation
- Stale predictive plans (> 24h) discarded
- No double-charge: if user clicks Generate manually after a predictive plan exists, the cached predictive plan is used

